
{{alias}}( p, λ, k )
    Evaluates the quantile function for a Weibull distribution with  with shape
    parameter `λ` and scale parameter `k` at a probability `p`.

    If provided `NaN` as any argument, the function returns `NaN`.

    If provided a nonpositive value for `λ` or `k`, the function returns `NaN`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    p: number
        Input value (probability).

    λ: number
        Scale parameter.

    k: number
        Shape parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    out: number
        Evaluated quantile function.

    Examples
    --------
    > var y = {{alias}}( 0.8, 1.0, 1.0 )
    ~1.609
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.5, 4.0, 2.0 )
    ~3.33
    > y = {{alias}}( 1.1, 1.0, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( -0.2, 1.0, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( NaN, 0.0, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.0, NaN, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.0, 0.0, NaN )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.5, 1.0, -1.0 )
    NaN


{{alias}}.factory( λ )
    Returns a function for evaluating the quantile function of a Weibull
    distribution with shape parameter `λ` and scale parameter `k`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    λ: number
        Scale parameter.

    k: number
        Shape parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    quantile: Function
        Quantile function.

    Examples
    --------
    > var myQuantile = {{alias}}.factory( 10.0, 2.0 );
    > var y = myQuantile( 0.4 )
    ~7.147
